Rating: 4
Excellent. I added garlic and cooked it a bit differently. I used a deeper dish, so the sauce covered more of the chicken, and after the chicken was cooked, I transferred the sauce to a pan with the butter and vermouth to cook on the stove top. It took about 2-3 times longer to cook (I just kept flipping the chicken to keep from burning). Both my husband and I loved it.

Rating: 0
In doing the whole "one new recipe each day" thing, I chose this one for Tuesday night this week and was really quite impressed. Unfortunately, the local supermarket was out of fresh oregano, so I substituted something else I had laying around, but the meal still turned out great and had my apartment smelling like taragon for the next day or so. I also chose the white wine over the vermouth, but I'll be attempting it with the original recommendation again in the near future. Either way, it turned out excellent. The only problem I experienced with the dish was that cooking it took significantly longer than the instructions, but I'm thinking this might actually be a function of the stove I was using. All in all, this is a great dish. I'll totally be whipping this up to impress friends in the near future.

Rating: 4
I just made this tonight and it was very delicious. The only problem I have is what results from broiling meat with an oil based marinade. I never did this before. Just a warning if you decide to make it, make sure the exhaust fan is on high, the windows are open wide and the battery is out of the smoke detector, with these instructions, there should be no problem. I would definitely make this again especially for invited guests! It's very easy and delicious!!

